So here=E2=80=99s a standard way to manipulate stocks:=09You buy a small, l=
ightly traded stock.=09You go on the message boards and say stuff like =E2=
=80=9CI hear this company has cured cancer, I=E2=80=99m buying all I can.=
=E2=80=9D=09The people on the message boards believe you and buy the stock,=
 so it goes up.=09You sell the stock for a profit.Here=E2=80=99s a =E2=80=
=A6=C2=A0basically just as standard? =E2=80=A6=C2=A0way to manipulate stock=
s:=09You buy a small, lightly traded stock.=09You go on a secret, password-=
protected, subscriber-only message board (or newsletter, love a newsletter)=
 and say =E2=80=9Chey I=E2=80=99m gonna publish fake rumors about this comp=
any to make its stock go up.=E2=80=9D=09Your subscribers buy the stock and =
it goes up.=09You go on the regular message boards and say stuff like =E2=
=80=9CI hear this company has cured cancer, I=E2=80=99m buying all I can.=
=E2=80=9D=09The people on the regular message boards believe you and buy th=
e stock, so it goes up more.=09You, and your special secret subscribers, se=
ll the stock for a profit.=09I guess you also charge for subscriptions?Ther=
e is no reason to stop there?=09Buy.=09Tip the super-secret, double-passwor=
d-protected, top-tier-subscribers only, whom you charge a ton of money.=09T=
ip the regular subscribers, whom you charge less money.=09Fake rumors to th=
e public.=09Sell, etc.Or add as many tiers of subscribers as you like; the =
more they pay you the earlier you tell them about your manipulations. But w=
hat about this:=09Buy.=09Tip your top-tier members.=09Tip your second-tier =
members.=09Sell.Leave out the fake rumors entirely. I mean I suppose in thi=
s one Step 3=C2=A0is a fake rumor, like, you say =E2=80=9CI am going to tel=
l people this stock cured cancer=E2=80=9D and then you don=E2=80=99t. But t=
hey can spread the rumors if they want, I don=E2=80=99t know. Or you can di=
spense with that too. Have a newsletter that is like =E2=80=9CMatt=E2=80=99=
s Stock Touts=E2=80=9D and each Wednesday you are like =E2=80=9Cthe stock t=
hat I have picked for this week is _______.=E2=80=9D No explanation, no rea=
son, no research, no analysis, no=C2=A0lies, just a  coordination game; =E2=
=80=9CI suggest that you buy this stock this week.=E2=80=9D And of course o=
n Tuesday you tell your top-tier subscribers in advance. And on Monday you =
tell your super-secret ultra-luxury-tier subscribers in advance.Why would t=
his work? Why does anything work. If you have no track record of moving sto=
ck prices no one will pay for your picks or buy based on them, but it sure =
seems like it=E2=80=99s not that hard to move the price of=C2=A0small illiq=
uid stocks, and once you do it twice maybe it=E2=80=99s a fun game for ever=
yone else. If you had asked me a year ago =E2=80=9Cif a dozen guys on inter=
net message boards decide for no reason to make a stock go up, can they do =
it?=E2=80=9D I would have said =E2=80=9CI don=E2=80=99t know, maybe, if it=
=E2=80=99s a small and illiquid stock.=E2=80=9D Now I=E2=80=99d just say =
=E2=80=9Coh yes that=E2=80=99s a very normal thing to happen=E2=80=9D; it=
=E2=80=99s been a weird year.Anyway here=E2=80=99s a Securities and Exchang=
e Commission enforcement action from last week:The Securities and Exchange =
Commission yesterday announced charges against Mark Melnick, the host of a =
stock trading webcast, for spreading more than 100 false rumors about publi=
c companies in order to generate illicit profits. The SEC previously charge=
d Barton Ross for his role in this scheme.According to the complaint, filed=
 in the United States District Court for the Northern District of Georgia o=
n September 30, 2021, Melnick received advance notice of companies about wh=
ich another scheme participant planned to spread false rumors, and then sha=
red the companies=E2=80=99 names with subscribers to his online trading roo=
m. Melnick advised the subscribers that he had taken positions in the compa=
nies, while other scheme participants also spread the false rumors through =
