tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;">everything is securities fraud</a>=E2=80=9D: Every bad thi=
ng that a public company does can be described as a fraud on its <em>shareh=
olders</em>, and then they (or the SEC) can sue. In particular, when a comp=
any pollutes or mistreats customers or harasses workers or whatever =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0when the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
25230754.274064/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzI=
wMjEtMDEtMDUvZHlzdG9waWFuLWZ1dHVyZS1zZWN1cml0aWVzLWZyYXVk/607f07ceef4b8524a=
