"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;">something like</a> =E2=80=9Cif Facebook keeps ge=
tting a reputation for not caring about safety people will stop using it or=
 it will be banned or something, I dunno but seems bad.=E2=80=9D</p><p styl=
e=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Those claims seem somewhat shaky to me.=C2=A0Do you t=
hink that world governments will come together to ban or limit oil drilling=
 to limit=C2=A0climate change? Do you think governments will regulate Faceb=
ook in a way that harms Facebook, or that users will flee over the most rec=
ent controversies? I dunno, maybe, but my tendency is to bet on inaction in=
 these areas.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But does it matter? If all th=
e shareholders of all the oil companies go to them and say =E2=80=9Cfind a =
way to stop drilling oil because eventually there will be laws against it,=
=E2=80=9D and the oil companies do what the shareholders want and pivot awa=
y from oil, and new oil projects can=E2=80=99t get financed because investo=
rs all think that they are not viable in the long run, then the problem is =
solved,=C2=A0<em>even if governments never actually pass laws against it</e=
m>. Shareholder assumptions about long-term viability can=C2=A0<em>create=
=C2=A0</em>(or destroy) long-term viability; the predictions about future r=
egulation don=E2=80=99t have to come true for this to work. Similarly, if F=
acebook=E2=80=99s shares drop due to whatever the latest controversy is, gu=
ess what, shareholders have a securities-fraud claim, even if whatever they=
 are worried about (regulation, loss of market share, etc.) never happens a=
nd the shares eventually recover.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And becau=
se the assumptions about future regulation or market reaction or whatever d=
on=E2=80=99t need to be true for this whole struture to work, nobody needs =
to emphasize them all that much. ESG investors can push for sustainability =
as a way to achieve long-term value without tying it directly to prediction=
s about regulation; oil companies have to plan for a lower-emissions world=
=C2=A0<em>because their shareholders tell them to</em>.</p><p style=3D"marg=
in: 16px 0;">And you can go to the SEC and say =E2=80=9CFacebook is harming=
 shareholders by putting profits over safety.=E2=80=9D Everyone understands=
, now, that profit=C2=A0is not the only thing shareholders want.</p><table =
